The paper deals with the problem of two mobile agents (robots) meeting in a bounded terrain, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO). The algorithms designed and analyzed in the paper involve constructing routes and making decisions based on the terrain and the robots' positions, which involves data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The robots are also subject to an adversary that can affect their movement, which involves control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the geometry of the terrain and obstacles, which involves computational geometry (cs.CG).
